						               													<description>By using simple to understand mechanics, such as playing cards and 'dice shifting', it is possible to simulate any of the troops who did the fightin` and a-dyin` a long way away from home or amongst their own cities and villages.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules attempt to embrace all the combatants who played a part in the war on both sides, from the Viet Cong guerrilla to the contributions made by Australia, South Korea and others (see 'Falling Dominoes' supplement).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim is the use of 28mm-sized figures, but 15 - 20mm miniatures may also be used with no real changes needing to be made.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is focused upon platoon level actions, although it should be possible to scale up or down as required (company to rifle squad).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
